    <string name="rules_title">Blokus rules</string>
    <string name="rules_youtube">Watch HowTo Video</string>
    <string name="rules_how_to_play">How to play</string>
    <string name="rules_how_to_play_1">Swipe the list of pieces to find and select the piece you want to play, then drag it onto the board.</string>
    <string name="rules_how_to_play_2">Touch the handles on the side of the piece to move, rotate and flip it into position. Tap the piece to place it onto the board.</string>
    <string name="rules_blokus_classic">Blokus Classic</string>
    <string name="rules_classic_1">Each player starts with 21 unique pieces in his color. Turn by turn every player tries to place a piece onto the board. The player with the most pieces on the board wins the game.</string>
    <string name="rules_classic_2">The first piece of each color must be placed in one of the corners of the board.</string>
    <string name="rules_classic_3">Each new piece played must be placed so that it touches at least one piece of the same color, with only corner-to-corner contact allowed. Edges cannot touch. However, edge-to-edge contact is allowed with pieces of different colors.</string>
    <string name="rules_classic_4">When a player cannot place a piece, he or she passes, and play continues as normal. The game ends when no one can place a piece.</string>
    <string name="rules_variants">Two player variants</string>
    <string name="rules_variants_1">Two players usually play with either two colors each, or by leaving out two colors.</string>
    <string name="rules_scoring">Scoring</string>
    <string name="rules_scoring_1">At the end, all squares of each player’s pieces on the board are added up (e.g. a “pentomino” is worth 5 points). If a player played all of their pieces, he gets a bonus score of +20 points if the last piece played was the single-square piece, +15 points otherwise.</string>
    <string name="rules_scoring_2">The maximum points a player can get in a game is therefore 89+20=109. The player with the highest score wins.</string>

    <string name="rules_duo_1">Blokus Duo is played by two players only on a much smaller board but with the same pieces as in Blokus Classic. The two starting squares are placed nearer to the centre.</string>
    <string name="rules_junior_1">Blokus Junior is targeted at younger children. Like Blokus Duo, it is played by two players on a 14×14 board but it uses only a subset of the pieces that have a simpler shape. There are 12 unique pieces, each player will get two of each kind.</string>
